com.github.tommyettinger.ds

Class IntList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.tommyettinger.ds.IntList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Arrangeable, java.io.Serializable

    public class IntList
extends java.lang.Object
implements Arrangeable, java.io.Serializable
    A resizable, ordered or unordered int list. Primitive-backed, so it avoids the boxing that occurs with an ArrayList of Integer. If unordered, this class avoids a memory copy when removing elements (the last element is moved to the removed element's position). This tries to imitate most of the List interface, though it can't implement it without boxing its items.

      • removeAll

        public boolean removeAll(IntList array)
        Removes from this array all of elements contained in the specified array. Note that if a value is present more than once in this IntList, only one of those occurrences will be removed for each occurrence of that value in array. If array has the same contents as this IntList or has additional items, then removing all of array will clear this.
        Returns:
        true if this array was modified.

      • iterator

        public IntList.IntListIterator iterator()
        Returns a Java 8 primitive iterator over the int items in this IntList. Iterates in order if ordered is true, otherwise this is not guaranteed to iterate in the same order as items were added.
        This will reuse one of two iterators in this IntList; this does not allow nested iteration. Use IntListIterator#IntListIterator(IntList) to nest iterators.
        Returns:
        a PrimitiveIterator.OfInt; use its nextInt() method instead of next()
